FRC 5951 Makers Assemble 2025 Build Thread | Open Alliance 2025 FRC Open Alliance
Software Update We are almost finished with our teleop code! Over the week, we mainly worked on several automations. Auto Reef Scoring Early in the season, we decided to take as much workload off the driver as possible. This led us to develop an almost fully automatic scoring system that requires the driver to simply hold the scoring button without any additional input. This is the complete automation: • Determine the target reef face based on distance, heading, and movement direction. • Ca…

We’re working now on making it more consistent and reliable, with the hopes of having it ready for Israel District 4 (more details to come soon on our OA thread)

We have an algae shooter, and it was pretty successful mechanically. If you set the power such that it barely clears the barge, bouncing out isn’t a huge issue. It’s definitely more prone to doing it on real barge than the practice barge though.

That said, while shooting algae was quick, we weren’t especially quick at acquiring it, and rarely used this capability outside of practice matches. So I can’t find any vods where we shot it. One of the only times we even grabbed it was our semifinal here, but should give you an idea of how we built it.
